Package statsVisualiser.gui

Class Analysis

java.lang.Object
statsVisualiser.gui.Analysis
Direct Known Subclasses:
A1_CO2VsEnergyVsAir, A2_AirVsForest, A3_CO2VsGDP, A4_Forest, A5_ExpEdPercentGDP, A6_HospitalVsHealthCosts, A7_HealthCostsVsInfants, A8_EdCosts
public abstract class Analysis
extends java.lang.Object
The base analysis class.

An abstract class that each Analysis will be built off of. This class contains basic information needed for each analysis, including the list of viewers to be displayed, the UI panel they will be displayed in, and an abstract calculate() method that must be implemented by each child of this class. Date: 4/2/2021

Author:
Olena Orlova, Cameron Arnold

    • calculate

      public abstract void calculate​(systemSelection selection)
      Performs the analysis calculation.

      Performs the following:

      1. Requests the data from the World Bank Database
      2. Performs the necessary calculations on the retrieved data (for example, gdp / population)
      3. Creates the ResultObject and populates it with the calculated data
      4. Triggers the ResultObject to create the viewers, fill them with data, and display them in the ViewerPanel in the MainUI


      Effects:
      • Creates the ResultObject
      • Modifies the Viewer Panel in the MainUI
      Parameters:
      selection - The data selected by the user (country, years, viewers, etc)
